               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace/>
                     <origDate>Copying date: First half of the 20th century. The church hierarchs liqa ṗāṗāsāt (“patriarch”)
                        Ṗeṭros and ṗāṗāsǝna (“our bishop/metropolitan”)  Yoḥannǝs are mentioned on fols. 9ra, 13ra-b, 17ra,
                        22rb, etc., but the resulting chronology is confusing. Coptic Patriarch Peter was in tenure in 1809-1852.
                        On fol. 22rb Peter is called the Alexandrian patriarch but a few lines below he is referred to as “our bishop” (ṗāṗāsǝna)
                        . Ethiopian Metropolitan Ṗeṭros was in tenure in 1881-1917. Another Bishop Ṗeṭros was for Wällo in 1928 (killed by the Italians in 1936).
                        The bishop Yoḥannǝs of Šäwa was installed in 1938. King Ḫayla Śǝllāse I (r. 1930-1974) is mentioned on fol. 82rb. </origDate>
                  </origin>
               </history>
